{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-16",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_16_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Third Murder",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 762.0,
  "page_end_sec": 1002.94,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.545,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 761.24,
      "end": 761.34,
      "text": "*While Effie Perine, her teeth chattering, fumbled with the corridor-door's lock",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 761.34,
      "end": 761.7,
      "text": "Spade knelt beside the thin man, turned him over on his back, and ran a hand down inside his overcoat."
    },
    {
      "start": 762.0,
      "end": 764.38,
      "text": "When he withdrew the hand presently"
    },
    {
      "start": 764.38,
      "end": 765.76,
      "text": "it came out smeared with blood."
    },
    {
      "start": 766.54,
      "end": 768.56,
      "text": "The sight of his bloody hand brought not the"
    },
    {
      "start": 768.56,
      "end": 771.02,
      "text": "least nor briefest of changes to Spade's face."
    },
    {
      "start": 771.94,
      "end": 774.14,
      "text": "Holding that hand up where it would touch nothing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 774.32,
      "end": 776.28,
      "text": "he took his lighter out of his pocket"
    },
    {
      "start": 776.64,
      "end": 777.38,
      "text": "with his other hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 778.18,
      "end": 779.62,
      "text": "He snapped on the flame and held the"
    },
    {
      "start": 779.62,
      "end": 781.82,
      "text": "flame close to first one and then the other"
    },
    {
      "start": 781.94,
      "end": 783.24,
      "text": "of the thin man's eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 783.94,
      "end": 784.3,
      "text": "The eyes—"
    },
    {
      "start": 784.52,
      "end": 785.02,
      "text": "lids,"
    },
    {
      "start": 785.14,
      "end": 785.5,
      "text": "balls,"
    },
    {
      "start": 785.68,
      "end": 786.16,
      "text": "irises,"
    },
    {
      "start": 786.16,
      "end": 787.4,
      "text": "and pupils—remained frozen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 787.74,
      "end": 788.26,
      "text": "immobile."
    },
    {
      "start": 789.248,
      "end": 792.06,
      "text": "Spade extinguished the flame and returned the lighter to his pocket.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 792.52,
      "end": 793.86,
      "text": "He moved on his knees"
    },
    {
      "start": 793.94,
      "end": 797.24,
      "text": "around to the dead man's side and, using his one clean hand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 797.71,
      "end": 799.4,
      "text": "unbuttoned and opened the tubular"
    },
    {
      "start": 799.66,
      "end": 799.98,
      "text": "overcoat."
    },
    {
      "start": 800.23,
      "end": 802.82,
      "text": "The inside of the overcoat was wet with blood"
    },
    {
      "start": 802.92,
      "end": 804.9,
      "text": "and the double-breasted blue jacket"
    },
    {
      "start": 804.96,
      "end": 805.88,
      "text": "beneath it was sodden."
    },
    {
      "start": 806.14,
      "end": 807.62,
      "text": "The jacket's lapels, where they crossed over the man's chest,"
    },
    {
      "start": 809.42,
      "end": 810.46,
      "text": "and both sides of"
    },
    {
      "start": 810.46,
      "end": 812.42,
      "text": "his coat immediately below that point,"
    },
    {
      "start": 812.42,
      "end": 814.36,
      "text": "were pierced by soggy ragged holes."
    },
    {
      "start": 815.392,
      "end": 816.64,
      "text": "Spade rose and went to the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 816.7,
      "end": 818.08,
      "text": "wash-bowl in the outer office."
    },
    {
      "start": 819.104,
      "end": 819.68,
      "text": "Effie Perine,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 819.8,
      "end": 820.6,
      "text": "wan and trembling"
    },
    {
      "start": 820.74,
      "end": 822.32,
      "text": "and holding herself upright by means"
    },
    {
      "start": 822.56,
      "end": 826.42,
      "text": "of a hand on the corridor-door's knob and her back against its glass,"
    },
    {
      "start": 826.52,
      "end": 827.02,
      "text": "whispered:"
    },
    {
      "start": 827.74,
      "end": 827.88,
      "text": "\"Is—"
    },
    {
      "start": 827.88,
      "end": 829.16,
      "text": "is he—?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 829.48,
      "end": 830.16,
      "text": "\"Yes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 831.2,
      "end": 833.48,
      "text": "Shot through the chest, maybe half a dozen times.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 833.66,
      "end": 835.38,
      "text": "Spade began to wash his hands."
    },
    {
      "start": 836.416,
      "end": 837.2,
      "text": "\"Oughtn't we—?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 837.8,
      "end": 838.22,
      "text": "she began,"
    },
    {
      "start": 838.44,
      "end": 839.66,
      "text": "but he cut her short:"
    },
    {
      "start": 840.48,
      "end": 841.82,
      "text": "\"It's too late for a doctor now"
    },
    {
      "start": 842.26,
      "end": 844.12,
      "text": "and I've got to think before we do anything.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 844.86,
      "end": 847.6,
      "text": "He finished washing his hands and began to rinse the bowl."
    },
    {
      "start": 848.5,
      "end": 850.22,
      "text": "\"He couldn't have come far with those in him."
    },
    {
      "start": 850.36,
      "end": 851.52,
      "text": "If he—"
    },
    {
      "start": 852.12,
      "end": 855.52,
      "text": "Why in hell couldn't he have stood up long enough to say something?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 856.12,
      "end": 857.42,
      "text": "He frowned at the girl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 857.56,
      "end": 858.64,
      "text": "rinsed his hands again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 858.72,
      "end": 859.64,
      "text": "and picked up a towel."
    },
    {
      "start": 860.54,
      "end": 861.36,
      "text": "\"Pull yourself together."
    },
    {
      "start": 862.34,
      "end": 863.04,
      "text": "For Christ's sake"
    },
    {
      "start": 863.08,
      "end": 864.4,
      "text": "don't get sick on me now!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 865.46,
      "end": 867.7,
      "text": "He threw the towel down and ran fingers through his hair."
    },
    {
      "start": 868.72,
      "end": 869.76,
      "text": "\"We'll have a look at that bundle.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 870.82,
      "end": 872.46,
      "text": "He went into the inner office again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 872.896,
      "end": 874.3,
      "text": "stepped over the dead man's legs,"
    },
    {
      "start": 874.4,
      "end": 876.62,
      "text": "and picked up the brown-paper-wrapped parcel."
    },
    {
      "start": 877.74,
      "end": 878.56,
      "text": "When he felt its weight,"
    },
    {
      "start": 878.64,
      "end": 879.78,
      "text": "his eyes glowed."
    },
    {
      "start": 880.36,
      "end": 881.5,
      "text": "He put it on his desk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 881.56,
      "end": 884.66,
      "text": "turning it over so that the knotted part of the rope was uppermost."
    },
    {
      "start": 885.42,
      "end": 886.54,
      "text": "The knot was hard and tight."
    },
    {
      "start": 887.1,
      "end": 889.26,
      "text": "He took out his pocket-knife and cut the rope."
    },
    {
      "start": 890.2,
      "end": 891.84,
      "text": "The girl had left the door and,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 891.94,
      "end": 894.7,
      "text": "edging around the dead man with her face turned away,"
    },
    {
      "start": 895.12,
      "end": 896.44,
      "text": "had come to Spade's side."
    },
    {
      "start": 897.5,
      "end": 898.18,
      "text": "As she stood there—"
    },
    {
      "start": 898.22,
      "end": 899.86,
      "text": "hands on a corner of the desk—"
    },
    {
      "start": 900.224,
      "end": 903.26,
      "text": "watching him pull the rope loose and push aside brown paper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 903.776,
      "end": 906.66,
      "text": "excitement began to supplant nausea in her face."
    },
    {
      "start": 907.68,
      "end": 908.46,
      "text": "\"Do you think it is?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 908.6,
      "end": 909.8,
      "text": "she whispered."
    },
    {
      "start": 910.56,
      "end": 911.12,
      "text": "\"We'll soon know,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 911.32,
      "end": 911.94,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 912.1,
      "end": 915.28,
      "text": "his big fingers busy with the inner husk of coarse grey paper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 915.66,
      "end": 916.5,
      "text": "three sheets thick,"
    },
    {
      "start": 916.68,
      "end": 918.8,
      "text": "that the brown paper's removal had revealed."
    },
    {
      "start": 919.94,
      "end": 921.36,
      "text": "His face was hard and dull."
    },
    {
      "start": 921.98,
      "end": 923.02,
      "text": "His eyes were shining."
    },
    {
      "start": 924.16,
      "end": 926.06,
      "text": "When he had put the grey paper out of the way"
    },
    {
      "start": 926.16,
      "end": 929.4,
      "text": "he had an egg-shaped mass of pale excelsior, wadded tight."
    },
    {
      "start": 930.36,
      "end": 931.78,
      "text": "His fingers tore the wad apart"
    },
    {
      "start": 931.92,
      "end": 934.54,
      "text": "and then he had the foot-high figure of a bird,"
    },
    {
      "start": 935.16,
      "end": 938.02,
      "text": "black as coal and shiny where its polish was not"
    },
    {
      "start": 938.02,
      "end": 940.8,
      "text": "dulled by wood-dust and fragments of excelsior."
    },
    {
      "start": 941.452,
      "end": 945.352,
      "text": "*Spade laughed. He put a hand down on the bird. His",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 945.352,
      "end": 945.812,
      "text": "wide-spread fingers had ownership in their curving."
    },
    {
      "start": 948.452,
      "end": 950.372,
      "text": "He put his other arm around Effie Perine and"
    },
    {
      "start": 950.892,
      "end": 954.032,
      "text": "crushed her body against his. \"We've got the damned"
    },
    {
      "start": 954.252,
      "end": 955.352,
      "text": "thing, angel,\" he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 956.152,
      "end": 959.132,
      "text": "\"Ouch!\" she said, \"you're hurting me.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 959.812,
      "end": 966.452,
      "text": "He took his arm away from her, picked the black bird up in both hands, and shook it to dislodge clinging excelsior."
    },
    {
      "start": 967.5,
      "end": 968.32,
      "text": "Then he stepped back",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 968.34,
      "end": 971.0,
      "text": "holding it up in front of him and blew dust off it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 971.04,
      "end": 972.37,
      "text": "regarding it triumphantly."
    },
    {
      "start": 973.728,
      "end": 975.98,
      "text": "Effie Perine made a horrified face and screamed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 976.18,
      "end": 977.22,
      "text": "pointing at his feet."
    },
    {
      "start": 977.6,
      "end": 979.12,
      "text": "He looked down at his feet.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 979.78,
      "end": 982.88,
      "text": "His last backward step had brought his left heel into contact"
    },
    {
      "start": 983.3,
      "end": 984.24,
      "text": "with the dead man's hand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 984.44,
      "end": 986.58,
      "text": "pinching a quarter-inch of flesh at"
    },
    {
      "start": 986.58,
      "end": 988.34,
      "text": "a side of the palm between heel and"
    },
    {
      "start": 988.46,
      "end": 988.6,
      "text": "floor."
    },
    {
      "start": 989.05,
      "end": 991.14,
      "text": "Spade jerked his foot away from the hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 991.4,
      "end": 993.18,
      "text": "The telephone-bell rang.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 993.46,
      "end": 995.08,
      "text": "He nodded at the girl.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 995.78,
      "end": 998.06,
      "text": "She turned to the desk and put the receiver to her ear."
    },
    {
      "start": 998.2,
      "end": 998.74,
      "text": "She said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 998.92,
      "end": 999.42,
      "text": "\"Hello. . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 999.7,
      "end": 1000.6,
      "text": "Yes. . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 1000.96,
      "end": 1001.06,
      "text": "Who? . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 1001.88,
      "end": 1002.62,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1002.62,
      "end": 1002.94,
      "text": "yes!\""
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}